The paper discusses representation learning in the context of graph mining, which is a common topic in the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also proposes a new method for network embedding, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on various tasks such as node classification, network reconstruction, and link prediction, which are common tasks in the subfields of data science (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB).
